In WordPress (or any CSS), you can specify a media query for screen widths between 769 and 1199 pixels using the `@media` rule. Here’s how you can write it:

```css
@media screen and (min-width: 769px) and (max-width: 1199px) {
    /* Your CSS styles here */
}
```

### Explanation:
- `@media screen` indicates that the styles will apply to screens (not print or other media types).
- `(min-width: 769px)` sets the minimum width condition.
- `(max-width: 1199px)` sets the maximum width condition.
- The styles you place within the curly braces will only apply when the screen width is between 769px and 1199px.

### Example:
```css
@media screen and (min-width: 769px) and (max-width: 1199px) {
    body {
        background-color: lightblue;
    }

    .header {
        font-size: 2em;
    }
}
```

This example will change the background color of the body and the font size of the header when the screen width is between 769 and 1199 pixels.
